mehraveh_tma :     Key control( Key &keys ,Graphic &graphicc)

mehraveh_tma :   {

mehraveh_tma :     keys.up= graphicc.upKeyPressed();

mehraveh_tma :     keys.right=graphicc.rightKeyPressed();

mehraveh_tma :     keys.left=graphicc.leftKeyPressed();

mehraveh_tma :     keys.down=graphicc.downKeyPressed();

mehraveh_tma :     return keys;

mehraveh_tma :   }

mehraveh_tma :    int update( Key &keys ,Graphic &graphicc ,int n)

mehraveh_tma :     {

mehraveh_tma :       static int i=0;

mehraveh_tma :       keys=control( keys ,graphicc);

mehraveh_tma :       if(keys.left)

mehraveh_tma :       {

mehraveh_tma :         i--;

mehraveh_tma :               keys.left=false;

mehraveh_tma :       }

mehraveh_tma :       if(keys.right)

mehraveh_tma :       {

mehraveh_tma :         i++;

mehraveh_tma :         keys.right=false;

mehraveh_tma :       }

mehraveh_tma :       if(keys.up)

mehraveh_tma :       {

mehraveh_tma :         i-=n;

mehraveh_tma :         keys.up=false;

mehraveh_tma :       }

mehraveh_tma :       if(keys.down)

mehraveh_tma :       {

mehraveh_tma :         i+=n;

mehraveh_tma :         keys.down=false;

mehraveh_tma :       }

mehraveh_tma :       if(i<0){

mehraveh_tma :         i=n*n-1-i;

mehraveh_tma :       }

mehraveh_tma :       return i%(n*n);

mehraveh_tma :     }

mehraveh_tma : فرزان تی ای درس مدار منطقی است. او از شاگردانش خواسته است که ساده سازی توابع سوییچینگ را به روش کویین-مک کلاسکی پیاده سازی کنند. فردی ناشناس با فرزان تماس می گیرد و ادعا می کند که شاگردان او تقلب می کنند. او حتی ادعا می کند که شخصی را که پاسخ را در اختیار دانشجویان قرار داده است می شناسد اما چون بسیار شاخ و خفن می باشد ترجیح می دهد نام متقلب را مستقیما نگوید. در عوض او تابع MM (مچ گیری متقلب) را طراحی کرده است که به ازای کلید های مختلف 4 عدد آخر شماره ی دانشجویی دانشجویان متقلب را در درس های مختلف، می دهد. با طراحی تابع MM به فرزان کمک کنید.

mehraveh_tma :  In computer science, an in-place algorithm is an algorithm which transforms input using no auxiliary data structure. However a small amount of extra storage space is allowed for auxiliary variables. The input is usually overwritten by the output as the algorithm executes. In-place algorithm updates input sequence only through replacement or swapping of elements. An algorithm which is not in-place is sometimes called not-in-place or out-of-place.

mehraveh_tma :     private GoogleMap mMap;

Override :     @Override

Override :     protected void onCreate(Bundle savedInstanceState) {

Override :         super.onCreate(savedInstanceState);

Override :         setContentView(R.layout.activity_maps);

Override :         // Obtain the SupportMapFragment and get notified when the map is ready to be used.

Override :         SupportMapFragment mapFragment = (SupportMapFragment) getSupportFragmentManager()

Override :                 .findFragmentById(R.id.map);

Override :         mapFragment.getMapAsync(this);

Override :     }

Override :     /**

Override :      * Manipulates the map once available.

Override :      * This callback is triggered when the map is ready to be used.

Override :      * This is where we can add markers or lines, add listeners or move the camera. In this case,

Override :      * we just add a marker near Sydney, Australia.

Override :      * If Google Play services is not installed on the device, the user will be prompted to install

Override :      * it inside the SupportMapFragment. This method will only be triggered once the user has

Override :      * installed Google Play services and returned to the app.

Override :      */

Override :     @Override

Override :     public void onMapReady(GoogleMap googleMap) {

Override :         mMap = googleMap;

Override :         // Add a marker in Sydney and move the camera

Override :         LatLng sydney = new LatLng(-34, 151);

Override :         mMap.addMarker(new MarkerOptions().position(sydney).title("Marker in Sydney"));

Override :         mMap.moveCamera(CameraUpdateFactory.newLatLng(sydney));

Override :     }

bangtansv :  Page faults can be handled in software because the overhead will be small
bangtansv : compared to the disk access time.

bangtansv :  Write­through will not work for virtual memory, since writes take too long.
bangtansv : Instead, virtual memory systems use write­back.

bangtansv :  The ability to use a clever
bangtansv : and flexible replacement scheme reduces the page fault rate and simplifies the use

bangtansv : of fully associative placement of pages.

bangtansv :  فولی ان اینا
bangtansv :  Each program has its own page
bangtansv : table, which maps the virtual address space of that program to main memory.

bangtansv :  [[Photo]]
bangtansv :  Once the operating system gets control, it must find
bangtansv : the page in the next level of the hierarchy (usually magnetic disk) and decide where

bangtansv : to place the requested page in main memory.

bangtansv :  Because we want to minimize the number of page faults, most operating
bangtansv : systems try to choose a page that they hypothesize will not be needed in the near

bangtansv : future. Using the past to predict the future, operating systems follow the least

bangtansv : recently used (LRU) replacement scheme

bangtansv :  [[Photo]]
bangtansv :  Implementing a completely accurate LRU scheme is too expensive, since it requires
bangtansv : updating a data structure on every memory reference. Instead, most operating

bangtansv : systems approximate LRU by keeping track of which pages have and which pages

bangtansv : have not been recently used. To help the operating system estimate the LRU pages,

bangtansv : some computers provide a reference bit or use bit, which is set whenever a page

bangtansv : is accessed.

bangtansv :  [[Photo]]
bangtansv :  virtual memory systems must use
bangtansv : write­back, performing the individual writes into the page in memory

bangtansv :  The dirty bit is
bangtansv : set when any word in a page is written

bangtansv :  [[Photo]]
bangtansv :  TLB misses will be much more frequent than true page
bangtansv : faults.

bangtansv :  we will need to select a TLB entry to replace. Because the reference and
bangtansv : dirty bits are contained in the TLB entry, we need to copy these bits back to the page

bangtansv : table entry when we replace an entry. These bits are the only portion of the TLB

bangtansv : entry that can be changed. Using write­back

bangtansv :  data
bangtansv : cannot be in the cache unless it is present in main memory. The operating system

bangtansv : helps maintain this hierarchy by flushing the contents of any page from the cache

bangtansv : when it decides to migrate that page to disk. At the same time, the OS modifies

bangtansv : the page tables and TLB, so that an attempt to access any data on the migrated page

bangtansv : will generate a page fault.

bangtansv :  [[Photo]]
bangtansv :  [[Photo]]
bangtansv :  When the cache is accessed with a virtual address and pages are shared between
bangtansv : programs (which may access them with different virtual addresses), there is the possibility

bangtansv : of aliasing. Aliasing occurs when the same object has two names—in this case, two

bangtansv : virtual addresses for the same page

bangtansv :  This ambiguity would allow one program to write the data without the
bangtansv : other program being aware that the data had changed

bangtansv :  physically addressed
bangtansv : cache A cache that is

bangtansv : addressed by a physical

bangtansv : address.

bangtansv :  بعد میگه بخاطر الیاسینگ
bangtansv :  فیزیکال ادرسی داشته باشیم مفید تر ممکنه باشه
bangtansv :  A TLB miss
bangtansv : can indicate one of two possibilities
bangtansv : 1. The page is present in memory, and we need only create the missing TLB entry.

bangtansv : 2. The page is not present in memory, and we need to transfer control to the

bangtansv : operating system to deal with a page fault.

bangtansv :  Once the operating system knows the virtual address that caused the page fault,
bangtansv : it must complete three steps
bangtansv : 1. Look up the page table entry using the virtual address and find the location

bangtansv : of the referenced page on disk.

bangtansv : 2. Choose a physical page to replace; if the chosen page is dirty, it must be written out to disk before we can bring a new virtual page into this physical page.

bangtansv : 3. Start a read to bring the referenced page from disk into the chosen physical

bangtansv : page.

bangtansv :  A TLB miss can be handled in software or hardware
bangtansv :  Page fault exceptions for data accesses are difficult to implement properly in a
bangtansv : processor because of a combination of three characteristics
bangtansv : 1. They occur in the middle of instructions, unlike instruction page faults.

bangtansv : 2. The instruction cannot be completed before handling the exception.

bangtansv : 3. After handling the exception, the instruction must be restarted as if nothing

bangtansv : had occurred.
